reviews.name: A D
reviews.text:
WARNING: RUN!!
Avoid this company at all costs. I hired Lutes Property for a small ceiling repair 08/2024 but the experience was a disaster. Despite repeated promises, they failed to show up on multiple scheduled dates, and when they finally did, the work was subpar (see attached photos). The owner, Brandon, initially offered to make it right but failed to follow through on his commitments and went silent. The company's lack of reliability, poor communication, and shoddy workmanship make them untrustworthy. Don't risk your time and money; take your business elsewhere.

reviews.name: Seth Abramson
reviews.text: Had an amazing experience with this company. My POC was Kristen and she was an excellent communicator. That’s what it’s all about at the end of the day. Communication and transparency. They took care of all my property needs with a single point of contact. What a breeze!

reviews.text: Had an emergency ac need at our retail business. An hour after calling on a thuraday at 5pm. A tech wad out to assess the situation and get a fix plan in progress. Great service all around.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText: Thank you so much for taking the time to leave us such a positive review! We're thrilled to hear that you had a great experience. If there's anything else we can assist you with in the future, please don't hesitate to reach out. We would be more than happy to help. Once again, thank you for choosing us!

reviews.name: Yevette Nina Linhart-Joseph
reviews.text: I used Lutes Property Services for years in the Charleston SC market for a wide variety of work on the multiple properties I managed in the area. My portfolio consisted of both class A office space and luxury single family properties requiring a high level of attention to detail and sensitivity to the client’s needs. I could always count on Lutes to provide the top notch service my clients expected, exactly when they needed it and always have a great attitude. They consistently delivered larger projects, on time and within budget, and I could always count on them in an emergency. If you have maintenance or construction needs in the greater Charleston area, make Lutes your first call.

reviews.name: Caroline Blackmon
reviews.text: Lutes Proper Services goes above and beyond to help with all of your property management needs. The staff is always very friendly, helpful and thorough-- especially Ashley, Donna & Jeremy! Jeremy is a funny, honest technician with a huge smile on his face when he's present. We are thankful for the team and all they do for us!

reviews.name: Coastal Carolina Family Dentistry
reviews.text: We love LPS! They take care of all of our normal monthly office maintenance items such as changing air filters, HVAC maintenance, light bulbs, emergency/exit lights, etc. On top of normal maintenance items they also have done major projects around the office/property -- we had a sidewalk extended, gate added, gutter repaired, dumpster enclosure painted and gate repaired, parking lot resurfaced and lines repainted, they've done some plumbing and electrical work while we were having new office equipment installed-- really they can do it all and they do it all well! They're a great team to work with and always make sure that we're taken care of!

reviews.name: Casa dei Girasoli
reviews.text: We can't say enough good things about Lutes Property Services.  Not only were they the first company to even bat an eye at our "small" commercial bid, they worked with us through our countless needs, changes and maintained professionalism every step of the way.  Their prices were competitive and reasonable for the tasks at hand.  Everyone there is respectful and kind; Amanda is one of the shining project coordinators whom you would be lucky to cross paths with. We are new business owners and they helped us make this process as painless as possible.  Thank you!
